show "=== v2d: parameterized composition reused on two lists ==="
remember an order called o1 with total as 75 and status as active
remember an order called o2 with total as 30 and status as pending
remember an order called o3 with total as 200 and status as active
remember a list called orders with o1 and o2 and o3
remember how to find-big from data: keep the data where total is above 50
find-big from orders

remember an order called o4 with total as 10 and status as active
remember a list called small-orders with o2 and o4
find-big from small-orders

show "=== v2d: value capture from parameterized composition (two from) ==="
remember the heavy called heavy from find-big from orders
count heavy

show "=== v2d: choose if/otherwise over a scalar ==="
remember a value called score with 75
choose if score is above 50: show "passing" otherwise show "failing"

show "=== v2d: multi-way branching with otherwise if ==="
remember a value called level with 5
choose if level is above 8: show "high range" otherwise if level is above 3: show "medium range" otherwise show "low range"

show "=== v2d: choose inside a composition (side effect only) ==="
remember how to classify from order: choose if total of order is above 100: show "premium" otherwise if total of order is above 50: show "standard" otherwise show "small"
classify from o1
classify from o2
classify from o3

show "=== v2d: multi-statement action via and inside a branch ==="
remember a value called points with 80
choose if points is above 50: show "qualified" and remember a value called tier with gold otherwise show "not qualified" and remember a value called tier with bronze
show tier

show "=== v2d: compound condition with and ==="
choose if total of o1 is above 50 and status of o1 is active: show "active big order"

show "=== v2d: compound condition with or ==="
choose if total of o2 is above 100 or status of o2 is pending: show "either-or matched"
